{"id":200746973,"lang":"python3","time":"2 years, 5 months","timestamp":1547316264,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"288 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/200746973/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"6.9 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def romanToInt(self, word):\n        table = {\n            **self._gen_nums('I', 'V', 'X', 1), \n            **self._gen_nums('X', 'L', 'C', 10),\n            **self._gen_nums('C', 'D', 'M', 100),\n            'M': 1000, 'MM': 2000, 'MMM': 3000,\n        }\n        num = 0\n        sub_str = ''\n        for char in word:\n            if (sub_str + char) not in table:\n                num += table[sub_str]\n                sub_str = char\n            else:\n                sub_str += char\n        num += table[sub_str]\n        return num\n    \n    @staticmethod\n    def _gen_nums(first, five, last, multiplier):\n        roman = [\n            first, \n            first + first, \n            first + first + first, \n            first + five, \n            five,\n            five + first,\n            five + first + first,\n            five + first + first + first,\n            first + last,\n        ]\n        return {rom: (num + 1)*multiplier for num, rom in enumerate(roman)}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer"}
